Date: Thu 14 Jul 2016
Source: Chillicothe Gazette [edited]
http://www.chillicothegazette.com/story/news/2016/07/14/pike-county-outbreak-longs-retreat/87099992/


Suspected outbreak of unknown illness hits Pike County [Ohio]
-------------------------------------------------------------
The Pike County Health District says "a suspected outbreak" of an unknown illness is affecting people who visited Long's Retreat Family Resort since 1 Jul 2016. As a result, the health district is asking people who visited the resort near Latham in July 2016 to contact its offices for an interview, even if they did not experience illness. In a news release, the district said some people reported nausea, vomiting, diarrhea and fever, but that "the origin of these symptoms is unclear, and nothing is confirmed."

Long's Retreat is working with the health district and the Ohio Department of Health to determine the cause of the illness. Officials there are exploring all areas, including water sources leading into the lake at Long's Retreat, the lake itself, possible food sources and concessions, restaurants, and camping sites.

