Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The symptoms described could well be norovirus. If it were, it is interesting to note that the prototype agent, the Norwalk virus, was 1st isolated in Norwalk, Ohio. Having an epidemic curve, the number of cases becoming ill per day can assist in deciding if this is a point source outbreak or one with a persistent source. Agents that readily transmit from person to person, causing secondary cases, however, can make the outbreak curve harder to interpret. The length of illness can help in the differential diagnosis but specific cultures or antigen tests will be diagnostic. Remember, in the case of sewage-contaminated drinking water or recreational water, there can be multiple agents occurring in the population. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4347998,35125.]
